.TH TB-PLUGIN 1 "December 2025" "ToolBox 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tb-plugin \- manage ToolBox plugins
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tb plugin
.I SUBCOMMAND
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B tb plugin
command manages ToolBox plugins. Plugins extend ToolBox functionality by adding new contexts and commands for specific workflows or technologies.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List all available plugins with their version, number of contexts, and enabled/disabled status
.TP
.B info
.I PLUGIN
Show detailed information about a specific plugin, including description, version, and available commands
.TP
.B contexts
List all available contexts from all plugins with their detection markers
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tb plugin list
Display all available plugins:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
NAME         VERSION   CONTEXTS   STATUS
────         ───────   ────────   ──────
kubernetes   1.0.0     2          enabled
ubuntu       1.0.0     1          enabled
docker       1.0.0     2          enabled
.fi
.in
.TP
.B tb plugin info ubuntu
Show detailed information about the Ubuntu plugin:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
Plugin: ubuntu
Version: 1.0.0
Contexts: 1

Context: ubuntu-packaging
  Description: Ubuntu/Debian packaging workflow
  
  Commands:
    gbranch          Create/checkout git branch
    ppa-status       Show PPA information
    dch-auto         Auto-update changelog
    ubuild           Complete build and upload workflow
    [... more commands ...]
.fi
.in
.TP
.B tb plugin contexts
List all available contexts from all plugins
.SH BUILT-IN PLUGINS
.SS Docker Plugin
Provides context for Docker and Docker Compose projects:
.TP
.B docker
For Dockerfile-based projects
.TP
.B docker-compose
For docker-compose.yml projects
.SS Kubernetes Plugin
Provides contexts for Kubernetes projects:
.TP
.B kubernetes
For projects with Kubernetes YAML manifests
.TP
.B helm
For Helm chart projects
.SS Ubuntu Plugin
Provides Ubuntu/Debian packaging workflow:
.TP
.B ubuntu-packaging
For projects with debian/ directory (debian/control, debian/changelog)
.br
Includes PPA-aware commands for managing Ubuntu package workflows
.SH PLUGIN DEVELOPMENT
Plugins are Go packages that implement the Plugin interface. See the Plugin Development Guide for creating custom plugins:
.PP
https://github.com/bamf0/toolbox/blob/main/docs/plugin-development.md
